Any substance which has the potential of degrading the environment is called an environmental hazard.
The hazards can be biological , chemical or nuclear majorly.
The biological hazards include the viruses or potential biological microorganisms which can result into a major infection breakout. 
The chemical hazards include chemical weapons and chemical substances which pollute and degrade the environment . 
The nuclear hazards include the chemical elements and isotopes which are very dangerous. 
Methods should be adopted to use the resources judiciously and not to degrade our environment.
